The agent A provided the following violation scenario:The memcpy calls within try_ready_chunked_body copy data into the write_buffer based on computed offsets and sizes, potentially risking out-of-bounds access if response->data_size, size_to_fill, or ret values are inconsistent or manipulated incorrectly. For example, when memcpy copies response->data[data_write_offset] into write_buffer[max_chunk_hdr_len] with length ret, if ret exceeds the remaining size of response->data from data_write_offset, it will access beyond bounds, violating Rule 21.17.
</scenario>
